 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service on Thursday said that Makhanda received most of the rain that fell on the Eastern Cape on Wednesday evening. "Although only 3 to 7 mm was measured over Port Elizabeth,  11 mm was recorded at Kouga Dam and Patensie," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. "The best figure for the last 2 days was the drought ravaged area of Grahamstown that  received a total of 47 mm. "The rainy weather will continue until Saturday when it will start cleaning over the western areas of the province." Station Names 5 6 Nelson Mandela Bay   AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport NIL 3.0 ARS 3rd Ave Dip NIL 5.2 ARS Blue Horizon Bay NIL 6.4 ARS Chatty NIL 5.0 AWS Coega NIL 1.0 AWSH Fettes Road NIL 4.4 ARS Flower Reserve NIL 7.4 AWSH Motherwell NIL * ARS Riverstone Bridge NIL 4.0 ARS St Albans NIL 5.2 AWS Uitenhage NIL 2.0 MAN Woodridge NIL 7.0 Catchment   AWS Joubertina NIL 2.2 ARS Kareedouw NIL 2.8 Man Kareedouw NIL 4.0 Man Kouga Dam NIL 11.5 AWS Patensie NIL 10.8 Man    Other Towns   AWS Addo 12.6 8.0 AWS Bisho/KWT NIL 0.6 AWS Cape St Francis NIL 4.6 AWS Cradock NIL 6.8 AWS East London NIL NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL 4.6 AWS George NIL NIL AWS Graaff Reinet 6.4 9.2 AWS Grahamstown 35.0 11.6 AWS Henry`s Flats NIL * AWS Joubertina NIL 2.2 AWS Mossel Bay NIL 2.8 AWS Mthatha NIL 0.6 AWS Plettenberg bay NIL 1.2 AWS Port Alfred NIL 10.2 AWS Queenstown 12.0 2.4  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 